Package com.redis.foundation.data

Class Data

java.lang.Object
com.redis.foundation.data.Data
public class Data extends Object
The Data class captures the constants, enumerated types and utility methods for the data package. Specifically, it defines the following:
  • Field data types
  • Date/Time and currency formatting constants
  • Data type conversion utility methods
Since:
1.0
Author:
Al Cole

    • nameToTitle

      public static String nameToTitle(String aName)
      Returns a title that has been derived from the name of the data item. This method will handle the conversion as follows:
      • id becomes Id
      • employee.name becomes Employee Name
      • employee_name becomes Employee Name
      • federatedName becomes Federated Name
      The logic will ignore any other conventions and simply pass the original character forward.
      Parameters:
      aName - Name of the data item to convert.
      Returns:
      Title for the data item name.

    • titleToName

      public static String titleToName(String aTitle)
      Returns a data item name that has been derived from the title. This method will handle the conversion as follows:
      • Id becomes id
      • Employee Name becomes employee_name
      • Federated Name becomes federated_name
      The logic will ignore any other conventions and simply pass the original character forward.
      Parameters:
      aTitle - Title string to convert.
      Returns:
      Data item name.
